WHEREAS, The members of the Senate of the 136th General Assembly 1
of Ohio are proud to commend the U.S. Marshals Service’s Northern Ohio 2
Violent Fugitive Task Force on the occasion of its 60,000 arrests, 3
March 24, 2025; and 4
WHEREAS, Established in 2003, the U.S. Marshals Service’s Northern 5
Ohio Violent Fugitive Task Force is a collaborative law enforcement 6
effort between federal, state, and local agencies that has provided a 7
unified offensive in the pursuit, apprehension, and prosecution of 8
violent adult fugitives across the northern district of the state. 9
Formed in direct support of Project Safe Neighborhoods, a nationwide 10
initiative to reduce gun crime in America, it has expanded to include 11
125 local police departments and sheriff’s offices, 350 law 12
enforcement personnel, and numerous outposts, and on March 24, 2025, 13
the U.S. Marshals Service’s Northern Ohio Violent Fugitive Task Force 14
was credited with securing its 60,000 arrests. This notable milestone 15
has provided further proof of the agency’s dedication to promoting 16
improved law enforcement methods that place the respect for law and 17
order at a premium; and 18
WHEREAS, All those who comprise the U.S. Marshals Service’s 19
Northern Ohio Violent Fugitive Task Force have made a measurable 20
difference in the State of Ohio and across the country, and they are 21
deserving of the highest praise for their expertise and commitment. 22
Indeed, their invaluable contributions have set a fine example of 23
humanitarian service, and their selfless endeavors to protect the 24
welfare of their fellow Ohioans stand as the hallmark of responsible 25

